### 1. Missing Body Parsing & Input Validation
The app has no middleware to parse request bodies, and no validation on any inputs (query params, headers, etc.).

### 2. No Error Handling Middleware
There's no global error handler, so unhandled errors will leak stack traces or crash the server.

### 3. Information Leakage on `/health`
Exposing server timestamps can be useful to attackers for timing attacks or fingerprinting.

### 4. No Rate Limiting
The endpoints have no protection against brute force or DoS attacks.

### 5. No Security Headers
Missing HTTP security headers (e.g., `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`).

### 6. Hardcoded Port
Port `3000` is hardcoded with no fallback to environment configuration.

---

